	<scenario>
                  <name>Cessna Invasion</name>
		<description>This scenario puts a fleet of Cessnas in the skies of San Francisco Bay near the San Francisco International Airport (KSFO).

The fleet starts just east of the airport and proceeds on a northerly heading at 1300 feet AGL.  If you take off runway 1R or 1L, when you get airborne look to your right and you will see a row of Cessnas there.

To aid visibility, by default the planes are "skywriters"--leaving a white trail of smoke behind.  Without the smoke trail the planes are nearly impossible to spot until you are right on top of them.

The Cessnas are air-to-air targets, you can damage them with heavy guns, machine guns, or (if you can hit them!) heavy bombs.
  
When you shoot or bomb the Cessnas they will catch fire, slow down, fall, and finally crash (to see the smoke and fire you must have Particles enabled in View/Rendering Options).

To damage the Cessnas takes one or more direct hits from a machine gun or heavy gun, or a close strike by a heavy bomb.   The Cessnas are fairly easy to damage and kill--if you can find and hit them!

Install this scenario in the FlightGear/data/AI directory.

Any aircraft that shoots guns or drops bombs can damage the Cessnas.  The Fairchild A-10 Thunderbolt is a great choice - http://wiki.flightgear.org/index.php/Fairchild_A-10
		</description>
		
